      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start for the core argument. To make it even more persuasive, I want to address the most common counter-arguments so I can debunk them effectively. \n\nMost people who oppose this idea talk about \"meritocracy\"—the idea that people should just keep what they earn through hard work. How can I frame the meritocracy argument in my essay so it looks like a weak or flawed concept compared to the need for redistribution? I want to show why the idea of a \"level playing field\" is actually a myth in this context.",
